Fluhrer rebounded with a win in the South Consolation bracket, winning 6-0, 6-3 In the Singles A - North Consolation Quarterfinals, Hemmerich dropped her match, 6-4, 6-1. Valdez and Vazquez both scored wins, taking their matches 6-1, 7-6 (10-8) and 7-5, 6-4, respectively. In the Singles B â€“ North Consolation, Calderon dropped her Quarterfinals match, 6-4, 6-1. "Michelle had a good win against Olga from USF. She is a good player that doesn't give you many free points, so you have to be disciplined and confident to beat her," added Cohen. "Quetzali also had a good win over Mina from Bethune-Cookman. Quetzali played more relaxed and effective tennis today, so I am happy for her." The Bedford Cup concludes tomorrow with the final day of action.
